  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Active surveillance among travelers and mobile populations in Ebola Virus Disease outbreak in North Kivu, Eastern Democratic Republic of the Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving health to vulnerable communities in regions affected by, and those at risk of, Ebola. This IOM project activates health screening points with hand-washing stations at strategic locations in the affected health zones, conducts contact tracking of known contacts with infected persons, and raises awareness and infection prevention and control measures. The project provides life-saving assistance to 595,000 people, including 121,000 women, 114,000 men, 360,000 children, and 105,000 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
